ulated dividend\npaid or declared, ur Under rule, n With\nwarrants, sw Without warrants, war War\nrants.\nRates of dividends in the foregoing table\nare annual disbursements based on the\nlast Quarterly or semi-annual declaration\nUnless otherwise noted, special or extra\ndlvidens are not included.\nDIVIDEND IS ORDERED\nBY APEX ELECTRICAL\nBy the Associated Press.\nCDEVELAND, Dec. 10.\u2014Directors\nof Apex Electrical Manufacturing Co.,\nmanufacturers of household appli\nances, declared a quarterly dividend\nof 30 cents a share on common stock\nand $1.75 on prior preferred stock.\nBoth dividends are payable December\n28 to stockholders of record Decem\nber 20.\nAIR TRAVEL DECLINES\nSHARPLY IN OCTOBER\nBy the Associated Press\nThe Air Commerce Bureau reports\nscheduled airlines carried 113,539 pas\nsengers 49,186,173 passenger miles in\nOctober, compared with 130.296 pas\nsengers transported 54,229,561 pas\nsenger miles in September.\nThey carried 684,241 pounds of ex\npress, or about 40,000 pounds less than\nthe previous month.\nSHARES ARE REGISTERED.\nThe United Combustion Oorp. of\nCleveland registered with the Securi\nties Commission yesterday an issue\nof 500 shares of $100 par preferred\nstock and 1,000 shares of SI par com\nmon stock. The company will act\nas Its own underwriter.\nBY RICHFIELD OIL\nInitial Payment of 25 Cents\na Share Is Ordered by\nBoard of Directors.\nBy the Associated Press.\nNEW YORK, Dec. 10.\u2014Directors of\nRichfield Oil Corp. today declared an\ninitial dividend of 25 cents, payable\nDecember 24 to holders of record De\ncember 16.\nGreyhound Corp.\nGreyhound Corp. announced an ex\ntra dividend on the common stock of\n50 cents a share, payable in 5% per\ncent preference stock at par, and a\nregular quarterly dividend of 20 cents,\nboth payable December 27 to holders\nof record December 17.\nWestinghouse Air Brake.\nIn line with the policy adopted in\nDecember, 1935, to distribute half of\nthe surplus to stockholders, directors\nof Westinghouse Air Brake declared\nanother special dividend of 25 cents\na share, payable January 31 of record\nDecember 2'\nGeneral Tire Sc Rubber.\nDirectors of Genera) Tire Rub\nber Co. announced the regular quar\nterly dividend of $1.50 a share on\npreferred stock, payable December 31\nto stock of record December 20.\n.i\u2014 m\nWashington Exchange\nSALES.\nWashington Gas pfd.\u20143 at 98 >4, 10\nat 99.\nWashington Railway Si Electric pfd.\u2014\n5 at 109, 10 at 109, 10 at 109, 10 at\n109.\nAFTER CALL.\nWashington Gas pfd.\u20145 at 99, 5 at\n99, 10 at 99. 10 at 99.\nPotomac Electric Power 6% pfd.\u20145\nat 113\u2019*.\nNotice\u2014The sale printed as of yes\nterday Potomac Electric 5l/a% pfd., 11\nat 11114, was canceled.\nBid and Asked Price*.\nBONDS.\nPUBLIC UTILITY.\nBid. Asked\nAmer. Tel A Tel 4 4s 100\nAnacostia Pot 5s __ 50 80\nAna. A Pot. Guar. 5s__ 107\nC. A P. Tel. ol Va. 5s __ 105\nCapital Traction R. R. 5s lid 70\nCity A Suburban 5s 50 60\nGeorgetown Gas 1st 5s 11.'!\nPot. Klee. Pow. li'is_ 102 104\nWash Gas 5s 1058. 104'4 JOO'j\nWash. Gas 5s 1060 1 1.'!\nWash. Rwy. A Elec. 4s ltitj _\nMISCELLANEOUS.\nChevy Chase Club 1st 4'\u00abs_102\nCol. Country Club 1st 4'.s 10.'! _ _\nW. M. Cold Storage 5s 100 _\nSTOCKS.\nPUBLIC UTILITY.\nAmer Tel. A Tel. _ _ 140\",\nCapital Transit Co .8 in'4\nN A W. Steamboat <61 6o HO\nPot. Elec. Pow 0% pfd i61 1 l.'i\nPot. El. Pow. 5,4r>. Pf. 15.50) Ill's\nWash. Gas Lt. new (1.20) 1H'4 2.'!\nWash Gas pld. <4.501 !I8'2 H9\nWash. Ry. A El. com. (g:!6) 600\nWash. Ry, A El. pfd. (51 108 1O0'2\nBANK AND TRUST COMPANY.\nAmer. See. A Tr. Co. (e8)__ 250 288\nBank of Bethesda (h.75)_ 34\nCapital (41 _ 125 145\nCom. A Savings (elO)_230\nLiberty (5) _ _ _ 14f)>2 180\nLincoln (16.25) 180 240\nNatl. Savings A Trust 225 275\nPr. Georees Bk. A Tr. (.50) 18 23\nRiggs (e8) 275 320\nRiggs pfd. (5) _ 101\nWashington <6i. 130\nWash. Loan A Trust (e8> 240 275\nFIRE INSURANCE\nAmerican (6) _ _ 112\nFiremen's <1.20' 28 _\nNational Union (.80) _ 14 _