 unchanged. Rubber shares were\nneglected, while German bonds sold lower.\nIron, steel and copper stocks were inclined\nto sair\nPARIS.\u2014International shares were In\nbetter demand in the Bourse and the\nIndustrial section was mixed. Govern\nment bonds eased and closed unchanged to\n80 centimes down, while Bank of France\nfained 160 francs. Royal Dutch lost 28\nrancs and Suez Canal moved up 25.\nODD-LOT DEALINGS.\nEj the Associated Press.\nThe Securities Commission reported to\nday these transactions by customers with\nodd-lot dealers or specialists on the New\nYork Stock Exchange for3 December 9:\n6,974 purchases involving 181.827 share*;\n5,038 sales involving 142.959 share*.\nPrice Changes in Chrysler Stock\ndollars Pricft* of Chryslor Stock 1933-1937 dollars\nPtR SHARE nR jHARt\nI I 1 Ewings' Earning*\n,40 Amounted to Earnings Amounted to\n$2.78 per Share\" Amounted to\nin 1933. Stock \u00ab2'.I9 oer Share !\u201935\u2018 Stoclt\n120\"' ho \u25a0!n ,9^- stock JUitS\n2.79 and 20.73 Sold Between 3.84 and 11.63\nlooll Tim*\u2018 EarnIn9* li 13.36 and 27.57 Earn,n9*\nEarnings\nAmounted to\n$14.25 per share\nin 1936. Stock\nSold Between --40\n6.12 and 9.74\nTimes Earnings\nJFMAMJJASON D J FMAMJJ ASON DJ FMAMJ JAS ONDJFMAMJ J A SON 0J FMAMJJ A SON 0\n1933 1934 1935 1936 1937\n^^Letters^AboyeAreJnitialsof^Months^JforJanuag^Ffor February, Etc.\nU. S. Steel Shows\nShipments Drop\nSmaller in Month\nBy the Associated Press.\nNEW YORK. Dec. 10 Shipments\nof finished steel products by sub\nsidiaries of the United States Steel\nCorp. In November decreased 205,069\ntons to 587,241 tons from 792,310 in\nOctober, the corporation announced\ntoday.\nIn the first 11 months this year\nshipments were 12,336.397 tons, an\nincrease of 2,578,630 tons over the\nlike period last year.\nThe decrease in shipments for No\nvember was 50.583 tons less than the\ndecrease in October shipments, as\ncompared with September, corpora\ntion official* said, indicating a slack\nening in the rate of decline.\nS. E. C. ISSUES REPORT\nON MEMBER DEALINGS\nBy the Associated Press.\nNew York Stock Exchange mem\nberg in the week ended November 13\ntraded 3.289.067 shares for their own\naccounts, or 22.21 per cent of total\ntransactions, the Securities and Ex-1\nchange Commission announced today, i\nIn the preceding week member trading i\nwas 21.54 per cent of all dealings.\nOf member round-lot dealings 7.65\nper cent was initiated on the floor of\nthe exchange, 3.95 per cent was in\nitiated off the floor, and 10.61 per cent\nwere specialists' transactions.\nTotal round-lot volume for the week\nended November 13 was 7,401,690\nshares, or 9 8 per cent larger than\nreported on the New York Stock Ex\nchange ticker.\nOn the New York Curb Exchange\nround-lot volume of member dealings\ntotaled 549,110 shares, or 20.87 per\ncent of total transactions. Curb\ntransactions of 1.315,290 shares ex\nceeded ticker volume by 10.2 per cent.\nINSURANCE STOCKS\nNEW YORK Dec. 10 upi.\u2014New York\nSecurity Dealers' Association:\nBid. Asked.\nAetna Cas (2a> _ 80 84\nAetna Ins (l.fiO)_ __ _ 40'2 4'\u2019>4\nAetna Life 80aI_ __ \".'l', *M\u00bb.\nAm Equit (1.80a)_ 253. \u00ab-\\4\nAm Ins Nwk t'2a>__ 10'2 12\nAm Reins (1.20b) __ 28 \"qi2\nAm Reserve (la) _ _ 183, 20'i\nAm Surety (2'jl _ fl?J. :w>.\nAutomobile (lai 241. 20'*\nBalt Amer (,20a) _ 43, 53\nCarolina (l.:t0) _ in'2 21\nCity of N Y (1.20) If3, 1 f\u00bb 12\nConn Gen Life (.80) _ 25',2 27\u2019\nContin Cas (1.201_ __ 2.1 \u00b05'i\nFid A- Deo <4a> xd \u00bb.V2 loo>,2\nFirems Nwk (.30)_ 7s. 0\nFrank Fire (la) _ _ 24\u2019. '\u2019ay.\nGen Reinsur (2)_ _ \u201d8 \"8\nGlen Falls (I.fiOi _ 35 37\nGlobe A Rep 80a) _ 123. 14'i\nGlobe A Rut 27'2 32>-2\nGreat Amer (la) _ __ ih34 oivl\nHanover (I.fiOi 27\"S*'.\nHartford Fi re (2) ______\nHornp Pir\u00bb Qee o I <11\nHome Ins <l*i __ 0412 op\nHomestead (I) __ 14'4 154;\nKnickerbocker (.80) _ ana,\nLincoln Fire _ '**3 3'2\nMaryland Cas _ _ 4*3\nMass Bond (3*4' 37 40\nMerc Ins Pr i,15g) 4 6\n